Originally, a transcript-wide U-content adjustment factor was calculated for the NHPMM and MCMC implementations. This was changed after simulations showed that performing the adjustment for groups of reads with the same mutational content increased robustness of the estimates to high read-to-read T-content variability (<ext-link xlink:href="http://www.rnajournal.org/lookup/suppl/doi:10.1261/rna.079451.122/-/DC1" ext-link-type="uri">Supplemental Figs. S18–S23</ext-link>). Results in all subsequent analyses were obtained with this modification. We used simulated data to confirm that the U-content adjusted Poisson mixture model performs as well as a binomial mixture model (<ext-link xlink:href="http://www.rnajournal.org/lookup/suppl/doi:10.1261/rna.079451.122/-/DC1" ext-link-type="uri">Supplemental Fig. S34</ext-link>).</p>
